20. Possumus equidem dicere] “We may surely say.” The common opinion, adopted among the Romans themselves, that equidem is a conti-action of eqo quidem, is refuted by the grammarian Priscian. Sciendum tamen quod quidam equidem conjunctionem compositam esse existimant ab eqo et quidem; sed errant. Simplex enim est. Et hoc maxime ex ipsa con- structione orationis possumus intelligere.
